Alright, it's boss time! Seems pretty basic to begin with, but I bet that'll change...
What does "Itadakimatsu" mean? (Apparently, it means something like "Let's eat" or "Bon Appetit", and it should be spelled "Itadakimasu", with the second "t" removed.)
Wow. I'm surprised I dodged that one. Also, screw checking that pipe.
Okay, I tried other buttons, and Select worked. So, apparently you can Start+Select out of this level at any time. But then, why did it say to press "R-L" instead of "Select"?
Anyway, I'm going to make some donations to recover some health now.
Of course, finding Rumia is another matter altogether, but she does just move in a simple side-to-side pattern like most other bosses in this hack.
Oh, but maybe I can reach them by bouncing off of these guys?
Cool, I got the ones I missed.

Click here to see where I got that sound clip from. (This was 8azaz22's idea.)

Okay, that was weird. When I hit Select while paused there, the game delayed for a few seconds, and then flashed a bunch of times before finally returning me to the overworld. I wonder why it did that?
Killer combo! (14 hits) (Of course, I did take a couple of hits myself...)
Alright, these four levels remain. So, place your votes for one of them, and we'll find out where I go next time!
This doesn't seem too bad, and I can see the bullets no matter where they are.
Alright, with Meet the darkness cleared, another segment of that path is revealed. Now, I'm going to reenter Meet the darkness, because I'm wondering one thing...
Ten stomps total ended that strobe light phase. Now comes the black sun again!
Hmm... I wonder if Rumia would like pasta...
Bad Apple!

Oh, man. After three stomps here, she's started tossing shurikens of darkness! I can still see them wherever they are, but the way they're thrown, dodging them while trying to stomp her is nearly impossible!
Stomping those bugs gradually dims the screen. I wonder if there's a way to restore the light...
To be continued...

Interestingly, I thought at first that The Scarlet Devil was going to win as I was tallying the votes, but then four of the last five votes were for Meet the darkness, which shot it out into first place!
